{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_016KJrc1uABtJ6cQctC9rcAw","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Development Guide: Multiarch Tuning Operator\n2\t\n3\t## Adding a Field to ClusterPodPlacementConfigSpec\n4\t\n5\tFollow these four steps in order. Skipping or reordering them will produce stale generated files.\n6\t\n7\t### Step 1 — Edit the API type\n8\t\n9\tOpen `api/v1beta1/clusterpodplacementconfig_types.go` and add the field to `ClusterPodPlacementConfigSpec`. Include kubebuilder validation markers:\n10\t\n11\t```go\n12\t// MyNewField describes what this field does.\n13\t// +optional\n14\t// +kubebuilder:default=\"somedefault\"\n15\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=optionA;optionB;\"\"\n16\tMyNewField string `json:\"myNewField,omitempty\"`\n17\t```\n18\t\n19\tAvailable types already in the spec for reference:\n20\t- `logVerbosity common.LogVerbosityLevel` — an enum-constrained string\n21\t- `namespaceSelector *metav1.LabelSelector` — optional label selector\n22\t- `plugins *plugins.Plugins` — optional nested struct\n23\t- `fallbackArchitecture string` — enum-constrained with allowed values `arm64;amd64;ppc64le;s390x;\"\"`\n24\t\n25\t### Step 2 — Run `make manifests` (MUST come before `make generate`)\n26\t\n27\t```bash\n28\tmake manifests\n29\t```\n30\t\n31\tThis regenerates:\n32\t- `config/crd/bases/multiarch.openshift.io_clusterpodplacementconfigs.yaml` — the CRD with your new field in `openAPIV3Schema`\n33\t- RBAC manifests in `config/rbac/`\n34\t\n35\tIf you run `make generate` before `make manifests`, DeepCopy implementations may reference a stale schema. Always run `make manifests` first.\n36\t\n37\t### Step 3 — Run `make generate`\n38\t\n39\t```bash\n40\tmake generate\n41\t```\n42\t\n43\tThis regenerates `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` files throughout the `api/` tree.\n44\t\n45\t### Step 4 — Wire through the CPPC informer\n46\t\n47\tControllers and the webhook must NOT call the Kubernetes API to read the CPPC at reconcile time. Instead, they read from the informer singleton:\n48\t\n49\t```go\n50\t// Correct: read from informer\n51\tcppc := clusterpodplacementconfig.GlobalCPPCSyncer.Get()\n52\t\n53\t// Wrong: do not do this in a hot reconcile path\n54\tvar cppc multiarchv1beta1.ClusterPodPlacementConfig\n55\terr := r.Client.Get(ctx, client.ObjectKey{Name: \"cluster\"}, &cppc)\n56\t```\n57\t\n58\tIf your new field needs to influence the webhook or controller behavior, add accessor logic to the informer package (`pkg/informers/clusterpodplacementconfig/`) so all consumers use the same in-memory object.\n59\t\n60\tIf the field needs validation beyond kubebuilder markers (e.g., cross-field constraints), add it to the validation webhook in `api/v1beta1/clusterpodplacementconfig_webhook.go` in the `ValidateCreate` / `ValidateUpdate` methods, not in the controller.\n61\t\n62\t## Adding a New Execution Mode\n63\t\n64\t### Conventions for leader election ID\n65\t\n66\tThe base ID is `208d7abd.multiarch.openshift.io`. Each mode prepends a unique prefix:\n67\t\n68\t```go\n69\tleaderID := \"208d7abd.multiarch.openshift.io\"\n70\tif enableMyNewMode {\n71\t    leaderID = fmt.Sprintf(\"mynewmode-%s\", leaderID)\n72\t}\n73\t```\n74\t\n75\tChoose a prefix that reflects the mode's function. Existing prefixes: `operator-`, `ppc-controllers-`, `enoexecevent-controllers-`.\n76\t\n77\t### Mutual exclusion in bindFlags\n78\t\n79\tAdd your flag variable and binding:\n80\t\n81\t```go\n82\tvar enableMyNewMode bool\n83\t\n84\t// in bindFlags():\n85\tflag.BoolVar(&enableMyNewMode, \"enable-my-new-mode\", false, \"Enable the my-new-mode controllers\")\n86\t```\n87\t\n88\tThen add it to `validateFlags()`:\n89\t\n90\t```go\n91\tfunc validateFlags() error {\n92\t    // count how many modes are enabled\n93\t    count := boolToInt(enableOperator) + boolToInt(enableClusterPodPlacementConfigOperandControllers) +\n94\t        boolToInt(enableClusterPodPlacementConfigOperandWebHook) + boolToInt(enableENoExecEventControllers) +\n95\t        boolToInt(enableMyNewMode)  // add here\n96\t    if count == 0 {\n97\t        return errors.New(\"at least one of the following flags must be set: ...\")\n98\t    }\n99\t    if count > 1 {\n100\t        return errors.New(\"only one of the following flags can be set: ...\")\n101\t    }\n102\t    return nil\n103\t}\n104\t```\n105\t\n106\t### CPPC informer startup\n107\t\n108\tIf your mode needs ClusterPodPlacementConfig configuration at runtime, set `enableCPPCInformer = true` in `bindFlags()` for your mode, or detect it in `main()`:\n109\t\n110\t```go\n111\tif enableMyNewMode {\n112\t    enableCPPCInformer = true\n113\t}\n114\t```\n115\t\n116\tThe CPPCSyncer is started unconditionally when `enableCPPCInformer` is true:\n117\t\n118\t```go\n119\tif enableCPPCInformer {\n120\t    must(mgr.Add(clusterpodplacementconfig.NewCPPCSyncer(mgr)), \"unable to instantiate CPPCSyncer\")\n121\t}\n122\t```\n123\t\n124\t### Implement the Run function\n125\t\n126\tCreate a `RunMyNewMode(mgr ctrl.Manager)` function (follow the pattern of `RunClusterPodPlacementConfigOperandControllers`) and call it from `main()`:\n127\t\n128\t```go\n129\tif enableMyNewMode {\n130\t    RunMyNewMode(mgr)\n131\t}\n132\t```\n133\t\n134\t## Code Generation Commands and Ordering\n135\t\n136\t| Command | What it does | When to run |\n137\t|---|---|---|\n138\t| `make manifests` | Regenerates CRD YAML, RBAC from kubebuilder markers | After editing any `api/` type with `+kubebuilder:` markers |\n139\t| `make generate` | Regenerates `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | After `make manifests`, when adding/removing fields |\n140\t| `make vendor` | Updates `vendor/` directory | After modifying `go.mod` or `go.sum` |\n141\t| `make verify-diff` | Fails if working tree has uncommitted generated files | Use in CI to catch missing regeneration |\n142\t\n143\tAlways run `make manifests` before `make generate`.\n144\t\n145\t## Running Tests\n146\t\n147\t### Unit tests (no cluster required)\n148\t\n149\t```bash\n150\t# All unit tests\n151\tmake unit\n152\t\n153\t# With verbose output and focused on a specific test\n154\tGINKGO_ARGS=\"-v --focus='should add scheduling gate'\" make unit\n155\t\n156\t# Run locally without Docker\n157\tNO_DOCKER=1 make unit\n158\t```\n159\t\n160\tUnit tests live alongside source files as `*_test.go` and use envtest for a fake API server.\n161\t\n162\t### Integration tests\n163\t\n164\tIntegration tests require a running cluster. They are part of `make test`:\n165\t\n166\t```bash\n167\tNO_DOCKER=1 make test\n168\t```\n169\t\n170\t### E2E tests (requires deployed operator)\n171\t\n172\t```bash\n173\tKUBECONFIG=/path/to/kubeconfig NAMESPACE=openshift-multiarch-tuning-operator make e2e\n174\t```\n175\t\n176\tE2E tests live in `pkg/e2e/` and validate full end-to-end behavior including actual image inspection.\n177\t\n178\t### Full check pipeline\n179\t\n180\t```bash\n181\tmake test  # runs manifests, generate, fmt, vet, goimports, gosec, lint, unit\n182\t```\n183\t\n184\tThis is what CI runs. Run it before submitting a PR.\n185\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c05c03ac-6c31-4e38-ab11-8699d11e4e32","uuid":"ad516d3d-b1e1-4b60-932a-16f31dbe905e","timestamp":"2026-07-20T18:04:22.688Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/multiarch-tuning-operator-treatment/agentic/DEVELOPMENT.md","content":"# Development Guide: Multiarch Tuning Operator\n\n## Adding a Field to ClusterPodPlacementConfigSpec\n\nFollow these four steps in order. Skipping or reordering them will produce stale generated files.\n\n### Step 1 — Edit the API type\n\nOpen `api/v1beta1/clusterpodplacementconfig_types.go` and add the field to `ClusterPodPlacementConfigSpec`. Include kubebuilder validation markers:\n\n```go\n// MyNewField describes what this field does.\n// +optional\n// +kubebuilder:default=\"somedefault\"\n// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=optionA;optionB;\"\"\nMyNewField string `json:\"myNewField,omitempty\"`\n```\n\nAvailable types already in the spec for reference:\n- `logVerbosity common.LogVerbosityLevel` — an enum-constrained string\n- `namespaceSelector *metav1.LabelSelector` — optional label selector\n- `plugins *plugins.Plugins` — optional nested struct\n- `fallbackArchitecture string` — enum-constrained with allowed values `arm64;amd64;ppc64le;s390x;\"\"`\n\n### Step 2 — Run `make manifests` (MUST come before `make generate`)\n\n```bash\nmake manifests\n```\n\nThis regenerates:\n- `config/crd/bases/multiarch.openshift.io_clusterpodplacementconfigs.yaml` — the CRD with your new field in `openAPIV3Schema`\n- RBAC manifests in `config/rbac/`\n\nIf you run `make generate` before `make manifests`, DeepCopy implementations may reference a stale schema. Always run `make manifests` first.\n\n### Step 3 — Run `make generate`\n\n```bash\nmake generate\n```\n\nThis regenerates `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` files throughout the `api/` tree.\n\n### Step 4 — Wire through the CPPC informer\n\nControllers and the webhook must NOT call the Kubernetes API to read the CPPC at reconcile time. Instead, they read from the informer singleton:\n\n```go\n// Correct: read from informer\ncppc := clusterpodplacementconfig.GlobalCPPCSyncer.Get()\n\n// Wrong: do not do this in a hot reconcile path\nvar cppc multiarchv1beta1.ClusterPodPlacementConfig\nerr := r.Client.Get(ctx, client.ObjectKey{Name: \"cluster\"}, &cppc)\n```\n\nIf your new field needs to influence the webhook or controller behavior, add accessor logic to the informer package (`pkg/informers/clusterpodplacementconfig/`) so all consumers use the same in-memory object.\n\nIf the field needs validation beyond kubebuilder markers (e.g., cross-field constraints), add it to the validation webhook in `api/v1beta1/clusterpodplacementconfig_webhook.go` in the `ValidateCreate` / `ValidateUpdate` methods, not in the controller.\n\n## Adding a New Execution Mode\n\n### Conventions for leader election ID\n\nThe base ID is `208d7abd.multiarch.openshift.io`. Each mode prepends a unique prefix:\n\n```go\nleaderID := \"208d7abd.multiarch.openshift.io\"\nif enableMyNewMode {\n    leaderID = fmt.Sprintf(\"mynewmode-%s\", leaderID)\n}\n```\n\nChoose a prefix that reflects the mode's function. Existing prefixes: `operator-`, `ppc-controllers-`, `enoexecevent-controllers-`.\n\n### Mutual exclusion in bindFlags\n\nAdd your flag variable and binding:\n\n```go\nvar enableMyNewMode bool\n\n// in bindFlags():\nflag.BoolVar(&enableMyNewMode, \"enable-my-new-mode\", false, \"Enable the my-new-mode controllers\")\n```\n\nThen add it to `validateFlags()`:\n\n```go\nfunc validateFlags() error {\n    // count how many modes are enabled\n    count := boolToInt(enableOperator) + boolToInt(enableClusterPodPlacementConfigOperandControllers) +\n        boolToInt(enableClusterPodPlacementConfigOperandWebHook) + boolToInt(enableENoExecEventControllers) +\n        boolToInt(enableMyNewMode)  // add here\n    if count == 0 {\n        return errors.New(\"at least one of the following flags must be set: ...\")\n    }\n    if count > 1 {\n        return errors.New(\"only one of the following flags can be set: ...\")\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### CPPC informer startup\n\nIf your mode needs ClusterPodPlacementConfig configuration at runtime, set `enableCPPCInformer = true` in `bindFlags()` for your mode, or detect it in `main()`:\n\n```go\nif enableMyNewMode {\n    enableCPPCInformer = true\n}\n```\n\nThe CPPCSyncer is started unconditionally when `enableCPPCInformer` is true:\n\n```go\nif enableCPPCInformer {\n    must(mgr.Add(clusterpodplacementconfig.NewCPPCSyncer(mgr)), \"unable to instantiate CPPCSyncer\")\n}\n```\n\n### Implement the Run function\n\nCreate a `RunMyNewMode(mgr ctrl.Manager)` function (follow the pattern of `RunClusterPodPlacementConfigOperandControllers`) and call it from `main()`:\n\n```go\nif enableMyNewMode {\n    RunMyNewMode(mgr)\n}\n```\n\n## Code Generation Commands and Ordering\n\n| Command | What it does | When to run |\n|---|---|---|\n| `make manifests` | Regenerates CRD YAML, RBAC from kubebuilder markers | After editing any `api/` type with `+kubebuilder:` markers |\n| `make generate` | Regenerates `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | After `make manifests`, when adding/removing fields |\n| `make vendor` | Updates `vendor/` directory | After modifying `go.mod` or `go.sum` |\n| `make verify-diff` | Fails if working tree has uncommitted generated files | Use in CI to catch missing regeneration |\n\nAlways run `make manifests` before `make generate`.\n\n## Running Tests\n\n### Unit tests (no cluster required)\n\n```bash\n# All unit tests\nmake unit\n\n# With verbose output and focused on a specific test\nGINKGO_ARGS=\"-v --focus='should add scheduling gate'\" make unit\n\n# Run locally without Docker\nNO_DOCKER=1 make unit\n```\n\nUnit tests live alongside source files as `*_test.go` and use envtest for a fake API server.\n\n### Integration tests\n\nIntegration tests require a running cluster. They are part of `make test`:\n\n```bash\nNO_DOCKER=1 make test\n```\n\n### E2E tests (requires deployed operator)\n\n```bash\nKUBECONFIG=/path/to/kubeconfig NAMESPACE=openshift-multiarch-tuning-operator make e2e\n```\n\nE2E tests live in `pkg/e2e/` and validate full end-to-end behavior including actual image inspection.\n\n### Full check pipeline\n\n```bash\nmake test  # runs manifests, generate, fmt, vet, goimports, gosec, lint, unit\n```\n\nThis is what CI runs. Run it before submitting a PR.\n","numLines":185,"startLine":1,"totalLines":185}}}
