efines the architecture to use if the image inspector cannot determine the image's architecture.\n\t// If configured, the PodPlacementController will set the node affinity of the pod to the fallback architecture\n\t// if the image inspector cannot determine the image's architecture.\n\t// +optional\n\t// +kubebuilder:default=\"\"\n\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=arm64;amd64;ppc64le;s390x;\"\"\n\tFallbackArchitecture string `json:\"fallbackArchitecture,omitempty\"`\n\n\t// MaxImageInspectionRetries defines the maximum number of times the pod placement controller\n\t// will retry image inspection when it fails to determine the supported architectures.\n\t// +optional\n\t// +kubebuilder:default=5\n\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n\t// +kubebuilder:validation:Maximum=20\n\tMaxImageInspectionRetries *int32 `json:\"maxImageInspectionRetries,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `internal/controller/podplacement/pod_model.go` — Replace hardcoded constant with CPPC informer lookup\n\nReplace the hardcoded constant and update `maxRetries()` to read from the CPPC informer.\n\n**Change 1:** Remove the constant (line 47):\n\n```go\n// DELETE this line:\nconst MaxRetryCount = 5\n```\n\nReplace with a default constant and a function that reads from the CPPC:\n\n```go\nconst DefaultMaxRetryCount = 5\n```\n\n**Change 2:** Add import for the CPPC informer package. In the import block, add:\n\n```go\n\t\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/informers/clusterpodplacementconfig\"\n```\n\n**Change 3:** Update `maxRetries()` (lines 389–398) to read from the informer:\n\n```go\nfunc (pod *Pod) maxRetries() bool {\n\tif pod.Labels == nil {\n\t\treturn false\n\t}\n\tv, err := strconv.ParseInt(pod.Labels[utils.ImageInspectionErrorCountLabel], 10, 32)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn true\n\t}\n\tmaxRetryCount := int64(DefaultMaxRetryCount)\n\tcppc := clusterpodplacementconfig.GetClusterPodPlacementConfig()\n\tif cppc != nil && cppc.Spec.MaxImageInspectionRetries != nil {